CM_ SG_ 784 ActvnOfLiForComity "signal send to actuator to activate dynamic light for comity function";
CM_ SG_ 784 ActvnOfLiForSpkr "signal send to actuator to activate dynamic light for showing speaker";
CM_ SG_ 784 ActvnOfLiForWait "signal send to actuator to activate dynamic light for wait function";
CM_ SG_ 784 CabPressPodCalc "Cabine pressure calculation for closing power operated doors. 0 Undefined, 1 VeryLow, 2 Low, 3 Medium, 4High, 5 VeryHigh";
CM_ SG_ 784 DoorDrvrLatPawlSt "Used to indicate if the driver door actuator must be triggered based in the pawl switch status AND other conditions from Driver door latch. [Close] Door is fully closed, the Pawl switch has changed value to PSD and timer to reach ajar is out without reaching ajar. [Open] Pawl Switch has not changed status to [PSD] OR latch successfully reach Ajar position within time. [Undefined] Not enough information about Pawl Switch status is found";
CM_ SG_ 784 DoorDrvrLatPosn "Driver door Cinch position. x01 equal fully open, x02 equal secondary position, x03 equal fully closed.";
CM_ SG_ 784 DoorLeReLatPawlSt "Used to indicate if the Left Rear door actuator must be triggered based in the pawl switch status AND other conditions from Left Rear door latch. [Close] Door is fully closed, the Pawl switch has changed value to PSD and timer to reach ajar is out without reaching ajar. [Open] Pawl Switch has not changed status to [PSD] OR latch successfully reach Ajar position within time. [Undefined] Not enough information about Pawl Switch status is found";
CM_ SG_ 784 DoorLeReLatPosn "Left rear door Cinch position. x01 equal fully open, x02 equal secondary position, x03 equal fully closed.";
CM_ SG_ 784 DoorPassLatPawlSt "Used to indicate if the passenger door actuator must be triggered based in the pawl switch status AND other conditions from passenger door latch. [Close] Door is fully closed, the Pawl switch has changed value to PSD and timer to reach ajar is out without reaching ajar. [Open] Pawl Switch has not changed status to [PSD] OR latch successfully reach Ajar position within time. [Undefined] Not enough information about Pawl Switch status is found";
CM_ SG_ 784 DoorPassLatPosn "Passenger door Cinch position. x01 equal fully open, x02 equal secondary position, x03 equal fully closed.";
CM_ SG_ 784 DoorRiReLatPawlSt "Used to indicate if the Right Rear door actuator must be triggered based in the pawl switch status AND other conditions from Right Rear door latch. [Close] Door is fully closed, the Pawl switch has changed value to PSD and timer to reach ajar is out without reaching ajar. [Open] Pawl Switch has not changed status to [PSD] OR latch successfully reach Ajar position within time. [Undefined] Not enough information about Pawl Switch status is found";
CM_ SG_ 784 DoorRiReLatPosn "Right rear door Cinch position. x01 equal fully open, x02 equal secondary position, x03 equal fully closed.";
CM_ SG_ 784 LockgCenStsLockSt "Signal LockgCenSts provides central locking status to other subsystems.
Signal is a record with three items
- LockSt (Lock State)
- TrigSrc (Trig Source)
- UpdEve (Will be set to TRUE during one second at each new central locking or unlocking event)";
CM_ SG_ 784 LockgCenStsTrigSrc "Signal LockgCenSts provides central locking status to other subsystems.
Signal is a record with three items
- LockSt (Lock State)
- TrigSrc (Trig Source)
- UpdEve (Will be set to TRUE during one second at each new central locking or unlocking event)";
CM_ SG_ 784 LockgCenStsUpdEve "Signal LockgCenSts provides central locking status to other subsystems.
Signal is a record with three items
- LockSt (Lock State)
- TrigSrc (Trig Source)
- UpdEve (Will be set to TRUE during one second at each new central locking or unlocking event)";
